HEADWORD: Fatidical
<hw>Fa*tid"i*cal</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fatidicus</ets>; <ets>fatum</ets> fate + <ets>dicere</ets> to say,
tell.]</ety> <def>Having power to foretell future events; prophetic;
fatiloquent; <as>as, the <ex>fatidical</ex> oak</as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <au>Howell.</au> --
<wordforms><wf>Fa*tid"i*cal*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

